Top ten list of quantum mechanics you encounter (241) Americium   6: Smoke detectors Most smoke detectors use the radioactive element Americium which emits alpha particles in their smoke detection. The alpha particles are released at a random, but fairly constant rate, and they create a current flow between two metal plates held at different voltages. When smoke enters, it changes the current and thereby is detected. The radioactive decay of Americium is a quantum phenomena, but not one we will discuss in detail in this class. Note that you should never dispose of a smoke detector in the garbage because of the radioactive material in it.   The Ouantum Wor und Us
